how to coordinate stenciling and colors on a bedroom wall my daughter wants to use different colors on her bedroom walls she will be stenciling the top edge of the walls how would you put all this together using colors good question try this identify which is the base color the accent color and then the trim color you could use the base color on two walls opposite of each other use the trim color on the other two walls use the accent color over the the stenciled trim area use the accent color over wood baseboards and trim components you can start with just a inch by inch spot of paint on the first and third opposite walls to see if you'll like it as far as the stenciled area identify which color you will be using for this once this is achieved it will be easier to identify the other colors sounds fun good luck jim Residual-current device Domestic AC power plugs and sockets Circuit breaker Screw Switch Fuse (electrical) Distribution board Tire Oscilloscope Industrial and multiphase power plugs and sockets Electrical wiring Violin Drill bit Ground and neutral Carburetor Three-phase electric power Mattress Aluminium Computer case Spark plug Oxy-fuel welding and cutting Rigging Seismic retrofit Floppy disk Wrench Ring circuit BS 1363 Upholstery Relay Nintendo GameCube RS-232 Wire wrap Poker jargon Gas metal arc welding Universal Serial Bus Capacitor Professional wrestling throws Tesla coil Glossary of firefighting equipment DVD Transformer Space Shuttle Solid Rocket Booster Enigma machine Solar cell Dog agility Overhead powerline Extension Cord Chess terminology Ethernet Softball Snooker Cable television Glossary of climbing terms Apollo Guidance Computer Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis 2004 U.S. presidential election controversy, voting machines Floyd Rose Printed circuit board TIA-568A/B Embedded system Elevator Wire Hydraulic machinery Burglar alarm Geodesic dome Fischer Random Chess Glossary of nautical terms Atari 8-bit family Antenna (radio) Ground (electricity) Weld